=Description=

"Open Media is a new concept going hand in hand with new media, citizen journalism, and all those fantastic buzzwords to come out of the Internet Age. Open Media advocates hold the concept that the content they create is fairly and freely distributed, while credit is still given to the creator. The creator can retain rights but still allow the content to move beyond boundaries and restrictions of the middle man. It is a relationship between the creator and the consumer.

Open Media can encompass everything from books to stories to video to music to art to even virtual worlds and games. It’s our goal to bring the newest information about open media, both in reviewing new content and bringing news in the world of open media to you."
(http://openmediareview.com/about-2/)


